parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ODS can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to potential injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light remains on or off
indicating that the airbag is not functioning properly
even when a passenger is seated and belted in. The light may illuminate randomly
and the airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning airbag sensor can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to potential injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag sensor fails to recognize the passenger
even when they are seated and belted in. The airbag light may remain on or off
indicating that the airbag is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent electrical system malfunction can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to potential injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The electrical system malfunctions intermittently
causing the airbag light to illuminate randomly
and the system may not respond to commands or communicate with paired cell phones.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
loses power
experiences sudden acceleration
has a sudden loss of propulsion
has difficulty shifting gears
makes a grinding noise
has an oil leak from the transfer case
and has a faulty torque converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to experience grinding noises, vibrations, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a grinding noise
vibrates while accelerating
has an oil leak from the transfer case
and experiences a sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to experience sudden acceleration, loss of power, and difficulty shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden acceleration
has difficulty shifting gears
and has a faulty torque converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to experience sudden loss of acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden loss of acceleration
bogging down of the engine
and difficulty accelerating from a dead stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to experience sudden loss of power and speed, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden loss of power and speed while locked in cruise control
engine over-revs
and loses speed and power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator can cause the anti-lock braking system to malfunction, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake warning light illuminates
the vehicle is unable to stop quickly
the brakes fail to respond
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to receive recall notifications or inadequate communication from the manufacturer can lead to delayed or missed repairs, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: No recall notification received
inadequate information provided
or lack of verification of recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake warning light illuminates
the vehicle is unable to stop quickly
and the brakes fail to respond.
